did.abstract: The collection consists of programs, statistics, press releases, scrapbooks, brochures, photographs, slides, video footage, and pamphlets pertaining to football, basketball, wrestling, golf, and other sports at Stanford University,

accessrestrict.head: Information about Access
accessrestrict.p: Collection is open for research; materials must be requested at least 48 hours in advance of intended use.

userestrict.head: Ownership & Copyright
userestrict.p: Property rights reside with the repository. Literary rights reside with the creators of the documents or their heirs. To obtain permission to publish or reproduce, please contact the Stanford University Archivist.

prefercite.head: Cite As
prefercite.p: [Identification of item], Stanford University, Department of Athletics, Communications, Records (SC0367). Department of Special Collections and University Archives, Stanford University Libraries, Stanford, Calif.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Content of Collection
scopecontent.p: The collection consists of programs, statistics, press releases, scrapbooks, brochures, photographs, slides, and pamphlets pertaining to football, basketball, wrestling, golf, and other sports at Stanford University, including two scrapbooks on women's sports at Stanford, 1964-1975. Also included are video tapes of football games, 1970-92; women's basketball games, 1987-99; men's basketball games, 1984-92; miscellaneous tapes of volleyball, swimming, gymnastics, and baseball; interviews with coaches Jack Elway, Dick Gould, Tara VanDerveer, and Mike Montgomery; and campus promotional spots aired during televised games.

bioghist.head: Biographical / Historical
bioghist.p: On March 12, 1975 all men’s and women’s sports programs were merged into a new Department of Athletics, Physical Education and Recreation (DAPER) to better enable the university to comply with Title IX. Stanford's first scholarships for women athletes are awarded in the fall. At the time, the university has 19 intercollegiate teams: 12 for men and seven for women.
